The paper introduces VEXUS, an interactive visualization framework for exploring user data. The paper focuses on the exploration of user groups, which is a common task in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The framework also involves indexing of user data, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions analyzing collective behaviors, which is a common task in social informatics (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SD).
